AutoLake

Automated Generation of Lakehouse Data Products from Semi-Structured Data

1. Executive Summary

AutoLake is an agentic developer tool that automates the creation of Lakehouse data products from semi-structured source data.

In many applications, operational data is stored in systems such as DynamoDB and later ingested into the Lakehouse. Although the data becomes centrally available, it often arrives as nested JSON or other semi-structured formats. This makes the data difficult to query directly and requires engineers to manually understand the source schema, identify nested relationships, design normalized tables, write transformations, and create materialized views.

AutoLake reduces this manual effort by analysing the source application and Lakehouse repositories, identifying the structure of the ingested data, proposing a normalized relational model, and generating the required Lakehouse artifacts.

The tool operates as a VS Code extension and keeps the developer in control through review and approval checkpoints. It does not directly deploy changes without validation. Instead, it generates reviewable code and configuration files, validates them, and creates a merge request for the final changes.

