11. Materialized Views

The generated materialized views serve as transformation and access layers on top of the raw ingested data.

AutoLake may generate two categories of materialized views.

11.1 Audit Materialized Views

Audit views preserve entity history and version-level information.

They are useful for:

* Tracking changes over time
* Debugging data issues
* Compliance analysis
* Reconstructing previous states

11.2 Latest Materialized Views

Latest views expose only the most recent version of an entity.

They are useful for:

* Business reporting
* Current-state analytics
* Downstream applications
* Simplified consumer queries

Keeping audit and latest views separate allows the data product to support both historical and operational use cases.

