12. Validation and Quality Controls

AutoLake applies quality checks at multiple levels.

Source Validation

The system confirms that the expected source entities, annotations and Lakehouse definitions are available.

Schema Validation

The normalized model is checked for missing keys, invalid references and unresolved types.

Artifact Validation

Generated PURE and materialized-view files are checked for structural consistency and required declarations.

Relationship Validation

Primary-key and foreign-key relationships are verified across all proposed tables.

Human Validation

The final schema proposal is reviewed before repository changes are created.

Repository Validation

The generated branch and merge request follow the existing source-control review process.

