13. Security and Governance

AutoLake follows the existing engineering governance model.

The main controls are:

* Credentials are retrieved from approved secret storage
* Secrets are not written to generated files
* Repository access follows the user’s existing permissions
* Every generated change is committed to a separate branch
* All changes are visible in a merge request
* Generated artifacts remain reviewable
* Important modelling decisions require human approval
* Pipeline outputs are stored for traceability and debugging

The system generates code, but the existing repository and review controls remain the source of authority.

