14. Key Design Principles

Artifact-Driven Pipeline

Every stage produces a structured artifact that becomes the input to the next stage. This makes the workflow traceable and resumable.

Human-Controlled Automation

The system automates repetitive work but keeps reviewers involved in decisions that require domain understanding.

Deterministic Where Possible

Normal program logic is used for tasks that do not require interpretation. LLMs are used only where reasoning adds value.

Review Before Integration

Generated changes are delivered through a merge request and are not directly merged or deployed.

Reusability

The pipeline is designed so that the same workflow can be applied to different services, entities and Lakehouse data products.

Failure Isolation

Each stage can fail, retry and resume independently. A failure in a later stage does not require the complete workflow to restart.

