16. Current Limitations

The current implementation has some limitations:

* Complex domain-specific relationships may still require manual correction
* Incomplete or inconsistent source annotations can reduce mapping accuracy
* Generated results depend on the quality of the source repositories
* Highly custom materialized-view logic may require developer changes
* LLM-generated proposals must still be reviewed
* The system currently focuses on supported repository and schema patterns
* End-to-end deployment remains outside the current scope

These limitations are handled through validation, confidence reporting and human review.

