18. Conclusion

AutoLake converts semi-structured Lakehouse data into structured and reusable data products through a guided automation workflow.

It analyses the source application and Lakehouse repositories, extracts the underlying data model, proposes a normalized schema, generates PURE and materialized-view artifacts, validates the output and creates a merge request for review.

The main value of AutoLake is not simply code generation. It standardizes and accelerates the complete process of understanding, modelling and publishing semi-structured data while keeping engineers in control of important decisions.

In simple terms:

AutoLake transforms raw semi-structured data already present in the Lakehouse into normalized, queryable and reviewable data products with significantly less manual engineering effort.